      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To calculate the impact, first, you need to determine the Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) and then factor in the value of the lost inventory due to shrinkage. The standard Inventory Turnover Ratio is COGS divided by Average Inventory, but you can adjust for shrinkage by increasing the COGS or decreasing the ending inventory value to reflect the actual goods available. This adjustment will show a higher effective cost relative to the remaining stock, thus lowering the turnover ratio as intended.",
